                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Does not require line of sight to damage enemies."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Base damage is 200 with a 20x damage multiplier, for an effective base damage of 4000 ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage falls off over distance, decreasing very sharply within just a few meters, then decreasing more slowly down to a minimum of 10% of the listed damage at the maximum range."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Falloff is based on the distance between Banshee and the target at the time of the ability hitting, not the distance the shockwave has traveled."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Moving closer to the target while the wave is traveling will increase the damage dealt, and vice versa."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Approximately follows the formula: Damage Multiplier = 0.1 * (distance / max range) -0.5"
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For some examples, the damage is reduced by 50% after traveling only 4% of its total range, and reduced by 75% after 16% ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage is bugged and fluctuates somewhat randomly. For example, an enemy further away from Banshee may take more damage than one closer to her, or two equally distant enemies may take noticeably different damage."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Resonating Quake",
                  "pageId": 987380,
                  "revisionId": 2729154,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The quake only hits enemies once per cast and pushes enemies back."
                }
              },
